<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1871,1969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1871,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species inhabits slow moving lowland streams inside the forest (between 0 and 
<specimenCount box="[1227,1299,1871,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1227,1295,1871,1896]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" unit="m" value="450.0">450m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
a.s.l.), from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,260,1908,1933]" name="Honduras" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Honduras</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[306,401,1908,1933]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, sharing its habitat with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="mitratum Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[700,882,1909,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="9" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mitratum" subSpecies="mitratum">
<emphasis box="[700,882,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">H. m. mitratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in some localities of the Central Cordillera in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,265,1944,1969]" name="Colombia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. New localities are recorded at 
<collectingRegion box="[617,690,1944,1969]" country="Colombia" name="Choco" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Chocó</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[744,856,1944,1969]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
departments (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1081,1944,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1999,2021]" captionTargetBox="[163,1421,1085,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1061,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Recorded localities in Colombia for H. aequatoriale, H. erythrogastrum and H. peregrinum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048661/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="562">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
